those who hate ds2 aren't a true souls fan. they just want a game that's hard. i dont know why people hated it. unpopular opinion, i think it has the best locations compared to any other souls game, except sekiro ofc. and the music...

but in terms of best fromsoft game, sekiro holds the title here, the soundtracks, characters, music, map everything is beyond perfect. this game is different, because unlike any soulsborne game, you cant roll out away; cowardly hiding behind roll iframes, you deeply understand boss patterns, and have to predict most boss moves from looking at their arms and position. and unlike any other soulsborne games, you dont find good weapons or sword/armors that makes the fight easier, or spawn summons. its only you and your kusabimaru, no matter what, the only thing that makes it easier is your improvement in skills, thats why many people say sekiro is the hardest fromsoft game, because they cant roll and hide behind iframes, nor they can get good weapons.

In my personal opinion the list of souls games goes like this
1. Elden ring
2.bloodborne
3.dark souls 2
4.dark souls 3
5.dark souls
6.demonâ€™s souls
7.sekiro
Hereâ€™s my reasoning.

Elden ring in my opinion has the most so far when it comes to lore and gameplay, you can play vastly different builds if you want, and there is so much you can do to where there is a lot of fun to have,etc. there are some downsides in this game such as boss movesets and hitboxes can be annoying but they are not all that bad.

Bloodborne is still a very good game with very fun gameplay, fun choices on weapons, boss designs are cool and a lot more, the general aggressive and faster gameplay is fun, etc. it is still what I believe would be a souls game while being different from all the others, I know that there are some parts most might not like such as having to farm healing items and ammo, and a few bosses are more gimmicky than fun, but that isnâ€™t all that bad.

Dark souls 2 has a lot that was added to the general mechanics of the game in comparison to the others. Thereâ€™s the red phantom enemies added in the different ng+ cycles, bonfire ascetics that allow you to send a specific area to the next ng+ level, they added power standing in this game,etc. I know some people donâ€™t like this game due to reasons such as the adaptability stat, hitboxes was another thing I saw some saying that were bad, and the boss run backs can be very annoying, but they really arenâ€™t all that bad as it seems.

Dark souls 3 is a refined version of the previous games in the series. The lore of this game does connect to the others, general gameplay is smoother, some general quality of life improvements, and the game in general plays quicker than the older games. While there arenâ€™t many Things that this game did bad, but other than minor improvements of general gameplay there not much else. This doesnâ€™t mean I think the game is bad.

Dark souls is a nostalgic experience with plenty of amazing lore, interesting npcs, and fun weapons and items to play with. There is a lot of good things with this game, but some downsides I would say would be how slow the general game is, the possibility of getting yourself semi stuck due to not being able to move between bonfires until about mid game, the later half of the game after anor londo seems rushed and quality drops a bit. Still this game is not bad.

Demonâ€™s souls is a fun game with the boss design being cool, the world tendency and character tendency mechanics are interesting, and you can have fun through out the game. I will say the game including the remake is overly slow and clunky, a large amount of the limited bosses are gimmick fights, the very small amount of bosses and linearity of the game areas makes it to were there is not a lot to do in the game, and only having one archstone per area that you makes it to were you have to unlock any and all shortcuts unless you want to fight through the entirety of the area to get back to the boss fight if you die can be annoying. Though it might look like I donâ€™t like this game that is not true, I do like this game a lot just in comparison to the others in my opinion it is lower but that does not mean it is by any means a bad game.

Sekiro is a fun new and challenging experience that is different from the other games, and there is interesting lore, good gameplay and some cool mechanics. I will say that this game has a few things that lowers it on this list. This game has the least amount of replay value due to there being very few changes you can make in what you can use, the really only weapon you can use is your katana (I know there are the prosthetic tools you can use but they are limited in the amount of times you can use them in between rests), and it gets pretty repetitive very quickly. The game is still good and it isnâ€™t a bad game but in comparison to all the other games it is the lowest.

Now this is just my opinion on this and if you donâ€™t agree that is perfectly ok.

In my personal opinion the list of souls games goes like this
1. Elden ring
2.bloodborne
3.dark souls 2
4.dark souls 3
5.dark souls
6.demonâ€™s souls
7.sekiro
Hereâ€™s my reasoning.

Elden ring in my opinion has the most so far when it comes to lore and gameplay, you can play vastly different builds if you want, and there is so much you can do to where there is a lot of fun to have,etc. there are some downsides in this game such as boss movesets and hitboxes can be annoying but they are not all that bad.

Bloodborne is still a very good game with very fun gameplay, fun choices on weapons, boss designs are cool and a lot more, the general aggressive and faster gameplay is fun, etc. it is still what I believe would be a souls game while being different from all the others, I know that there are some parts most might not like such as having to farm healing items and ammo, and a few bosses are more gimmicky than fun, but that isnâ€™t all that bad.

Dark souls 2 has a lot that was added to the general mechanics of the game in comparison to the others. Thereâ€™s the red phantom enemies added in the different ng+ cycles, bonfire ascetics that allow you to send a specific area to the next ng+ level, they added power standing in this game,etc. I know some people donâ€™t like this game due to reasons such as the adaptability stat, hitboxes was another thing I saw some saying that were bad, and the boss run backs can be very annoying, but they really arenâ€™t all that bad as it seems.

Dark souls 3 is a refined version of the previous games in the series. The lore of this game does connect to the others, general gameplay is smoother, some general quality of life improvements, and the game in general plays quicker than the older games. While there arenâ€™t many Things that this game did bad, but other than minor improvements of general gameplay there not much else. This doesnâ€™t mean I think the game is bad.

Dark souls is a nostalgic experience with plenty of amazing lore, interesting npcs, and fun weapons and items to play with. There is a lot of good things with this game, but some downsides I would say would be how slow the general game is, the possibility of getting yourself semi stuck due to not being able to move between bonfires until about mid game, the later half of the game after anor londo seems rushed and quality drops a bit. Still this game is not bad.

Demonâ€™s souls is a fun game with the boss design being cool, the world tendency and character tendency mechanics are interesting, and you can have fun through out the game. I will say the game including the remake is overly slow and clunky, a large amount of the limited bosses are gimmick fights, the very small amount of bosses and linearity of the game areas makes it to were there is not a lot to do in the game, and only having one archstone per area that you makes it to were you have to unlock any and all shortcuts unless you want to fight through the entirety of the area to get back to the boss fight if you die can be annoying. Though it might look like I donâ€™t like this game that is not true, I do like this game a lot just in comparison to the others in my opinion it is lower but that does not mean it is by any means a bad game.

Sekiro is a fun new and challenging experience that is different from the other games, and there is interesting lore, good gameplay and some cool mechanics. I will say that this game has a few things that lowers it on this list. This game has the least amount of replay value due to there being very few changes you can make in what you can use, the really only weapon you can use is your katana (I know there are the prosthetic tools you can use but they are limited in the amount of times you can use them in between rests), and it gets pretty repetitive very quickly. The game is still good and it isnâ€™t a bad game but in comparison to all the other games it is the lowest.

Now this is just my opinion on this and if you donâ€™t agree that is perfectly ok.
